From: Martin Pluskal <mpluskal@suse.com>
Subject: Do not fail metadata generation when git is unavailable
Upstream: https://github.com/thuml/depyf/pull/94

setup.py's get_version() shells out to `git rev-parse HEAD` to append a
commit id to the version. In a source-tarball build (no git binary, no
repository) the subprocess raises FileNotFoundError, which the handler
does not catch, aborting metadata generation. Catch it alongside
CalledProcessError so the clean release version from depyf/VERSION.txt
is used.

--- a/setup.py
+++ b/setup.py
@@ -11,7 +11,7 @@
         # Decode bytes to string (Python 3.x)
         commit_id = commit_id.decode('utf-8')
         return commit_id[:n_digits]
-    except subprocess.CalledProcessError as e:
+    except (subprocess.CalledProcessError, FileNotFoundError) as e:
         print("Failed to get Git commit ID:", e)
         return None
 
